{"key":"post-17906853","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17906853</id>\n<content>Don't use cal-mag.&amp;nbsp; That's for people growing plants in soft water.&amp;nbsp; Don't use peroxide as that's not a pH buffer at all, and don't use potassium silicate either.&amp;nbsp; As a matter of fact, don't pay $3/pint for water!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mushroom mycelium thrives and grows best in a pH of around 5 to 5.5.&amp;nbsp; We only lime casing layers as a way to slow down molds which hate a high pH even more than mushroom mycelium.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Use calcium carbonate or hydrated lime to adjust pH when necessary.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17914298</next>\n<prev>17906536</prev>\n<first>17906464</first>\n<last>17915173</last>\n<when>1362493342</when>\n<utime>03/05/13 04:22 PM</utime>\n</post>"}